00:28:28,441 --> 00:28:30,410
'No, nothing.'

735
00:28:32,946 --> 00:28:34,515
Anything at all?

736
00:28:34,548 --> 00:28:37,150
No, ma'am.

737
00:28:37,183 --> 00:28:38,519
The feeling will
come back, won't it?

738
00:28:38,552 --> 00:28:41,487
That's what the doctors
are trying to find out.

739
00:28:41,522 --> 00:28:43,524
Ouch!
Oh, I felt that.

740
00:28:43,557 --> 00:28:45,325
Good.
Good. Mark it.

741
00:28:45,358 --> 00:28:47,761
Sir, we're going to
watch you very closely.

742
00:28:47,794 --> 00:28:50,230
If the swelling in your
spinal cord continues

743
00:28:50,263 --> 00:28:52,398
we may have to put you on a
ventilator to help you breathe.

744
00:28:52,432 --> 00:28:55,268
I got a hold of a baby‐sitter
at your house, Mr. Williams.

745
00:28:55,301 --> 00:28:56,537
She said your wife
was at school.

746
00:28:56,570 --> 00:28:58,839
Oh, that's right,
it's, um, it's Thursday.

747
00:28:58,872 --> 00:29:00,941
She won't get in
until midnight.

748
00:29:00,974 --> 00:29:03,009
Okay, we'll get
a message to her.

749
00:29:03,043 --> 00:29:05,045
Get that baby‐sitter
on the phone, now.

750
00:29:05,078 --> 00:29:06,046
Okay.

751
00:29:06,980 --> 00:29:08,014
Malik.

752
00:29:08,048 --> 00:29:10,016
Malik, hold on!
Damn it!

753
00:29:10,050 --> 00:29:12,853
‐ I'll bring it back.
‐ 'I need it now!'

754
00:29:12,886 --> 00:29:15,088
‐ Kerry, I was about to do‐‐
‐ Jeanie it's Morgenstern.

755
00:29:15,121 --> 00:29:16,790
Oh, my God.

756
00:29:28,434 --> 00:29:29,536
'What you got, Carter?'

757
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:31,004
The kid who got
beat up earlier.

758
00:29:31,037 --> 00:29:32,372
He crashed before
we could get a CT.

759
00:29:32,405 --> 00:29:34,541
Lavage was positive.
It may be his spleen.

760
00:29:34,575 --> 00:29:36,109
Is it the kid with
the head trauma?

761
00:29:36,142 --> 00:29:38,344
Yeah, you've to get in line.
I need a CT.

762
00:29:38,378 --> 00:29:40,280
No time, you'll have to drill
the burr holes up in OR.

763
00:29:40,313 --> 00:29:41,848
Let's move.
Carter, where are you going?

764
00:29:41,882 --> 00:29:43,517
Up. I'm bagging him.
Not anymore. Go move.

765
00:29:43,550 --> 00:29:45,151
‐ Dr. Benton.
‐ Thank you.

766
00:29:47,921 --> 00:29:50,390
Somebody's disappointed
I left surgery, isn't he?

767
00:29:50,423 --> 00:29:51,858
Excuse me, I'm Ms. Corday.

768
00:29:51,892 --> 00:29:54,194
Could you point me
towards casualty?

769
00:29:54,227 --> 00:29:55,862
Sorry, trauma.
I mean trauma.

770
00:29:55,896 --> 00:29:58,031
‐ Trauma is that way.
‐ Do you need any help?

771
00:29:58,064 --> 00:29:59,933
No, I'll call out
if I get lost.

772
00:29:59,966 --> 00:30:01,367
You okay?

773
00:30:01,401 --> 00:30:03,469
Kid was trying
to get out of a gang.

774
00:30:03,504 --> 00:30:05,271
You're in the
ER, Carter.

775
00:30:05,305 --> 00:30:07,107
Get them on the elevator alive,
you've done your job.

776
00:30:07,140 --> 00:30:08,408
How do you think
he's gonna do?

777
00:30:08,441 --> 00:30:09,976
He's got a blown
left pupil

778
00:30:10,010 --> 00:30:11,912
probably means
a chronic vegetative state

779
00:30:11,945 --> 00:30:13,514
if he doesn't
bleed to death first.

780
00:30:15,081 --> 00:30:16,550
How bad does he look?

781
00:30:16,583 --> 00:30:19,853
His STs are sky high
in two, three, and F.

782
00:30:19,886 --> 00:30:22,589
His father had an MI at 40.
Yeah, I'll hold.

783
00:30:22,623 --> 00:30:24,625
Hey, Dr. Weaver, I wonder
if we could talk now..

784
00:30:24,658 --> 00:30:27,160
‐ Later.
‐ He's throwing PVC's.

785
00:30:27,193 --> 00:30:29,129
‐ Should we give him lidocaine?
‐ Yes. Great.

786
00:30:29,162 --> 00:30:31,131
Cath lab's ready for us.
Let's get him up.

787
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:36,102
Dr. Greene, I wonder if you're
aware of my situation..

788
00:30:36,136 --> 00:30:37,370
'I got the baby‐sitter.'

789
00:30:37,403 --> 00:30:38,972
Later, Carter.

790
00:30:39,005 --> 00:30:40,273
Excuse me.

791
00:30:41,942 --> 00:30:43,476
Is this
the Williams' sitter?

792
00:30:43,510 --> 00:30:45,211
Hello, this is Dr. Greene

793
00:30:45,245 --> 00:30:48,014
from the emergency room
at County General Hospital.

794
00:30:48,048 --> 00:30:50,316
Do you understand me?

795
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:54,588
How far away are you from where
Mrs. Williams goes to school?

796
00:30:54,621 --> 00:30:57,190
Good, get a neighbor
to watch the baby

797
00:30:57,223 --> 00:31:00,260
and run there as fast
as you can and get her.

798
00:31:00,293 --> 00:31:03,229
Tell her it's an emergency
and that every minute counts.

799
00:31:03,263 --> 00:31:04,364
Put her in a cab.

800
00:31:04,397 --> 00:31:07,367
We're about
a ten‐minute ride away.

801
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,135
You got all that?

802
00:31:09,169 --> 00:31:10,537
Any questions?

803
00:31:10,571 --> 00:31:12,906
Good. Go.

804
00:31:12,939 --> 00:31:14,508
'Is he losing his
ability to breathe?'

805
00:31:14,541 --> 00:31:15,976
At the rate his
pulse ox is falling

806
00:31:16,009 --> 00:31:18,111
I'll be forced
to intubate him soon.

807
00:31:18,144 --> 00:31:20,914
'So, you need the wife here to
sign a consent or something?'

808
00:31:20,947 --> 00:31:22,448
Mr. Williams is paralyzed

809
00:31:22,482 --> 00:31:23,984
probably for the rest
of his life.

810
00:31:24,017 --> 00:31:25,318
Right now,
he can still speak.

811
00:31:25,351 --> 00:31:27,087
It would be nice
if he and his wife

812
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:30,390
could talk to each other for a
few minutes while he still can.

813
00:31:30,423 --> 00:31:32,926
Theo, can you take
a deep breath for me?

814
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,562
Good.

815
00:31:35,596 --> 00:31:36,930
I'll see if Dr. Greene
can join us.

816
00:31:36,963 --> 00:31:38,298
Good idea.

817
00:31:38,331 --> 00:31:39,966
Excuse me, nurse.
I'm Ms. Corday.

818
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,501
I was beeped down
for a consult.

819
00:31:41,535 --> 00:31:45,071
You're a doctor?
Oh, don't mind them.

820
00:31:45,105 --> 00:31:47,407
These gentlemen are
making a movie.

821
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:50,343
Yes, I'm a surgical lecturer
in orthopedics and trauma.

822
00:31:50,376 --> 00:31:52,513
They said there was
an adolescent who decompensated.

823
00:31:52,546 --> 00:31:54,247
Oh, Dr. Benton took him up.

824
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:55,616
Ah, Dr. Benton.

825
00:31:55,649 --> 00:31:56,983
You call your
surgeons "Doctor."

826
00:31:57,017 --> 00:31:58,218
Well, I suppose "Ms. Corday"

827
00:31:58,251 --> 00:31:59,319
won't get me very
far around here.

828
00:31:59,352 --> 00:32:00,987
Just to the waiting room.

829
00:32:01,021 --> 00:32:03,524
‐ I'm Carol Hathaway.
‐ 'Pleasure meeting you.'

830
00:32:03,557 --> 00:32:04,991
'So, how did the
patient look?'

831
00:32:05,025 --> 00:32:06,560
'The boy with the
positive lavage?'

832
00:32:06,593 --> 00:32:08,595
Not good,
blown pupil, deep coma.

833
00:32:08,629 --> 00:32:12,165
‐ This the kid I saved?
‐ Yeah.

834
00:32:12,198 --> 00:32:13,667
We're keeping
our fingers crossed.

835
00:32:16,570 --> 00:32:17,638
David, are you still
experiencing

836
00:32:17,671 --> 00:32:20,106
the same amount
of pain? Okay.

837
00:32:20,140 --> 00:32:23,443
On a scale of one to ten how
would you rate that pain?

838
00:32:23,476 --> 00:32:25,078
'Uh, ei‐eight.'

839
00:32:25,111 --> 00:32:26,312
‐ Pardon? Eight.
‐ Eight.

840
00:32:26,346 --> 00:32:28,715
Okay, let's get him
on very gently

841
00:32:28,749 --> 00:32:30,016
and they're all
set up for us.

842
00:32:30,050 --> 00:32:31,351
'They know we're coming.'

843
00:32:31,384 --> 00:32:32,519
‐ 'Here we go.'
‐ What the hell..?

844
00:32:32,553 --> 00:32:33,587
Hey, what are you doing?

845
00:32:33,620 --> 00:32:35,388
No. No. I asked
you not to.

846
00:32:35,421 --> 00:32:37,558
‐ 'You going to the cath lab?'
‐ Yes. Turn it off.

847
00:32:37,591 --> 00:32:39,392
'Isn't there an another patient
who's been waiting for hours?'

848
00:32:39,425 --> 00:32:41,394
What? What do you mean?

849
00:32:41,427 --> 00:32:42,629
'Do some patients get
preferential treatment'

850
00:32:42,663 --> 00:32:44,731
'in the ER?'

851
00:32:44,765 --> 00:32:46,667
Look at me.
I'm talking to you.

852
00:32:46,700 --> 00:32:48,334
‐ Is this recording?
‐ 'Yes.'

853
00:32:48,368 --> 00:32:50,036
Good, because I want to know.
Are you a doctor?

854
00:32:50,070 --> 00:32:52,138
Do you have experience
with myocardial infarctions?

855
00:32:52,172 --> 00:32:53,173
‐ 'No.'
‐ How's he doing?

856
00:32:53,206 --> 00:32:54,374
Sinus rhythm 60,
pulse ox 96.

857
00:32:54,407 --> 00:32:56,476
Look at me, then
how can you make

858
00:32:56,510 --> 00:32:58,344
an accusation about
patient treatment?

859
00:32:58,378 --> 00:33:00,714
Just because your camera sees
a picture of one man going

860
00:33:00,747 --> 00:33:03,449
to the cath lab, you assume
preferential treatment!

861
00:33:03,483 --> 00:33:05,418
Do you know what acute
ST elevations are?

862
00:33:05,451 --> 00:33:07,588
Is there another patient in the
ER who had a run of V‐tach?

863
00:33:07,621 --> 00:33:09,222
'I don't know.'

864
00:33:09,255 --> 00:33:10,724
‐ How's the ectopy?
‐ 'Under five per minute.'

865
00:33:10,757 --> 00:33:12,125
So, what do you want
to know?

866
00:33:12,158 --> 00:33:16,462
‐ What can we tell you?
‐ 'I'm sorry.'

867
00:33:16,496 --> 00:33:18,264
'I got carried away.'

868
00:33:18,298 --> 00:33:19,299
You did.

869
00:33:25,105 --> 00:33:26,106
What have you got?

870
00:33:26,139 --> 00:33:27,273
82‐year‐old male

871
00:33:27,307 --> 00:33:28,809
found down
at his nursing home.

872
00:33:28,842 --> 00:33:31,244
Went in fib en route,
shocked twice without success.

873
00:33:31,277 --> 00:33:32,579
‐ 'Shall I defibrillate?'
‐ 'Be my guest.'

874
00:33:32,613 --> 00:33:34,447
‐ Charge to 360.
‐ 'You got it.'

875
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:36,216
‐ Has he had EPI?
‐ Yup. Three minutes ago.

876
00:33:36,249 --> 00:33:39,452
‐ 'Go ahead.'
‐ Lube it up.

877
00:33:39,485 --> 00:33:41,622
‐ Three‐sixty? Clear.
‐ Yeah.

878
00:33:41,655 --> 00:33:43,489
'Agi, I need a battery.'

879
00:33:43,524 --> 00:33:46,326
'Another 50 of lidocaine.
Do it again, 360.'

880
00:33:46,359 --> 00:33:47,661
'Agi, my camera
battery's dying!'

881
00:33:47,694 --> 00:33:50,597
'Keep shooting, Stuart.

882
00:33:50,631 --> 00:33:52,398
‐ 'Got a rhythm.'
‐ Pulse?

883
00:33:52,432 --> 00:33:55,135
'Faint, but it's there.'

884
00:33:55,168 --> 00:33:56,369
Alright, everybody,
we got him back!

885
00:33:56,402 --> 00:33:57,604
‐ Good work.
‐ 'I'm losing power.'

886
00:33:57,638 --> 00:33:59,339
'How's that feel, doctor?'

887
00:33:59,372 --> 00:34:00,607
To bring somebody back?

888
00:34:00,641 --> 00:34:02,576
Oh, that's the, uh,
that's the, um..

889
00:34:10,250 --> 00:34:11,618
‐ Dr. Benton?
‐ Yeah?

890
00:34:11,652 --> 00:34:13,186
Elizabeth Corday.

891
00:34:13,219 --> 00:34:15,188
Visiting surgical lecturer
and your savior.

892
00:34:15,221 --> 00:34:16,623
Excuse me.

893
00:34:16,657 --> 00:34:18,692
You've been on call forever.
You're free to go.

894
00:34:18,725 --> 00:34:22,162
‐ I'm on now.
‐ Oh, I'm sorry.

895
00:34:22,195 --> 00:34:23,530
Excuse me,
are you the doctor

896
00:34:23,564 --> 00:34:24,698
who was taking care
of my brother?

897
00:34:24,731 --> 00:34:26,099
Yeah.
You're still down here?

898
00:34:26,132 --> 00:34:27,634
Yeah, I had to talk
to the cops.

899
00:34:27,668 --> 00:34:30,103
‐ Oh.
‐ Oh, sorry.

900
00:34:30,136 --> 00:34:31,605
How is he?

901
00:34:31,638 --> 00:34:33,574
Well, they removed his spleen
to stop the bleeding

902
00:34:33,607 --> 00:34:35,275
and the neurosurgeons
are still working on him.

903
00:34:35,308 --> 00:34:36,843
Does he have brain damage?

904
00:34:36,877 --> 00:34:39,279
Let's call upstairs and see
if there's any news, okay?

905
00:34:39,312 --> 00:34:42,415
‐ Here we go.
‐ I thought I was a goner.

906
00:34:42,448 --> 00:34:44,250
Yeah? Me, too.

907
00:34:44,284 --> 00:34:45,652
You'll be getting
a lot of "Thank‐you's"

908
00:34:45,686 --> 00:34:49,122
from the female population
over at Riverview.

909
00:34:49,155 --> 00:34:50,490
I don't want to brag
too much, but‐‐

910
00:34:50,524 --> 00:34:52,626
Yeah. You a pretty popular
guy over there?

911
00:34:52,659 --> 00:34:56,730
Well, I seem to be.

912
00:34:56,763 --> 00:34:59,633
I never was much of
a Casanova in my day.

913
00:34:59,666 --> 00:35:04,170
I didn't go in for all the wild
positions and so forth.

914
00:35:04,204 --> 00:35:06,540
But the ladies need that,
you know, all the positions.

915
00:35:06,573 --> 00:35:08,341
So I've heard.

916
00:35:08,374 --> 00:35:09,776
And the sweet talk.

917
00:35:09,810 --> 00:35:11,812
I never was much
for that either.

918
00:35:11,845 --> 00:35:15,415
You know, I was mostly
meat and potatoes.

919
00:35:15,448 --> 00:35:19,352
But now, I'm 82,
I'm a man, I'm breathing

920
00:35:19,385 --> 00:35:22,388
the odds are 12‐1
in my favor.

921
00:35:22,422 --> 00:35:24,658
I'm getting it
anytime I want.

922
00:35:25,726 --> 00:35:27,861
Not too bad, old age.

923
00:35:27,894 --> 00:35:29,896
I'm glad to hear it.

924
00:35:29,930 --> 00:35:31,832
Tell you, it feels good
to save the life of a man

925
00:35:31,865 --> 00:35:35,669
who's performing
such a service to society.

926
00:35:35,702 --> 00:35:38,271
Stud service.

927
00:35:38,304 --> 00:35:39,606
Get that in.

928
00:35:41,908 --> 00:35:43,844
He was found down outside
the Stones concert.

929
00:35:43,877 --> 00:35:45,311
He looked like he fell through

930
00:35:45,345 --> 00:35:47,380
a sheet of plate
glass or something.

931
00:35:47,413 --> 00:35:49,650
‐ Easy. Easy.
‐ No, no, no, no.

932
00:35:49,683 --> 00:35:51,552
Leave me alone.
Stop. Stop. Stop.

933
00:35:51,585 --> 00:35:53,386
‐ Get away! Don't touch me!
‐ Call security.

934
00:35:53,419 --> 00:35:54,788
Security!

935
00:35:54,821 --> 00:35:57,257
Alright, alright, alright.
Everything's okay.

936
00:35:57,290 --> 00:35:58,592
It's alright.
Just relax.

937
00:35:58,625 --> 00:36:01,928
No, stay away.
Stay away!

938
00:36:01,962 --> 00:36:03,730
I‐m‐I'm sick.
Okay. Just stay away from me.

939
00:36:03,764 --> 00:36:05,866
‐ Okay. It's okay.
‐ No, it's not okay.

940
00:36:05,899 --> 00:36:07,367
‐ It's alright.
‐ I'm sick.

941
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:09,936
I'm HIV‐positive, okay.
I've got aids.

942
00:36:09,970 --> 00:36:12,773
Stay away from me.

943
00:36:12,806 --> 00:36:16,376
‐ Please. No, no.
‐ Stop.

944
00:36:16,409 --> 00:36:18,378
Shh.
It's okay.

945
00:36:18,411 --> 00:36:21,381
Alright? Just lay back.

946
00:36:21,414 --> 00:36:22,415
Let us help you.

947
00:36:22,448 --> 00:36:23,884
‐ Don't..
‐ It's okay.

948
00:36:23,917 --> 00:36:26,452
‐ It itches.
‐ I know it itches.

949
00:36:26,486 --> 00:36:28,188
Just take it away.

950
00:36:29,389 --> 00:36:30,957
I'll take it away, okay?

951
00:36:30,991 --> 00:36:35,261
Lay back. It's okay.
Shh. Come on.

952
00:36:35,295 --> 00:36:36,630
We'll make it better, okay.

953
00:36:36,663 --> 00:36:39,633
‐ Help me.
‐ I'll do what I can.

954
00:36:45,672 --> 00:36:48,542
'So when did you decide
to become a surgeon?'

955
00:36:48,575 --> 00:36:51,545
Oh, well, uh, that gets
into pleasing my father

956
00:36:51,578 --> 00:36:54,748
rattling my mother and all sorts
of boring family secrets.

957
00:36:54,781 --> 00:36:56,950
But the short answer is
my father is a surgeon

958
00:36:56,983 --> 00:37:00,754
as was his father
and my father had no sons.

959
00:37:00,787 --> 00:37:03,524
'Are you a resident
in the UK?'

960
00:37:03,557 --> 00:37:05,491
Well, I'm afraid it's a
different system altogether.

961
00:37:05,526 --> 00:37:07,694
Um, I'm an FRCS which is

962
00:37:07,728 --> 00:37:10,597
a Fellow of the Royal College
of Surgeons and a lecturer.

963
00:37:10,631 --> 00:37:13,934
That's roughly the equivalent of
your senior surgical residents

964
00:37:13,967 --> 00:37:16,837
but not really,
because I have six..

965
00:37:16,870 --> 00:37:19,806
I'm sorry. You can't possibly
be interested in this.

966
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:21,542
Dr. Benton?

967
00:37:21,575 --> 00:37:24,277
Please rescue me from
these well‐intentioned people.

968
00:37:24,310 --> 00:37:26,680
'We're just talking about
the surgical service.'

969
00:37:26,713 --> 00:37:28,582
Listen, have you seen that young
lady I was talking to earlier?

970
00:37:28,615 --> 00:37:29,983
The sister of the
boy up in surgery?

971
00:37:30,016 --> 00:37:31,685
Yeah, I got some news
and I can't find her.

972
00:37:31,718 --> 00:37:33,720
‐ I'll keep my eyes open.
‐ Alright, thank you.

973
00:37:37,758 --> 00:37:39,693
Paralyzed?

974
00:37:39,726 --> 00:37:41,361
For good?

975
00:37:41,394 --> 00:37:42,863
It's too early to say
if your husband's

976
00:37:42,896 --> 00:37:46,900
going to have any
recovery of function.

977
00:37:46,933 --> 00:37:48,769
What did he think
he was doing?

978
00:37:48,802 --> 00:37:51,371
He was trying to
save a boy's life.

979
00:37:51,404 --> 00:37:52,739
I know.

980
00:37:52,773 --> 00:37:54,340
Your husband is very
eager to talk to you.

981
00:37:54,374 --> 00:37:56,309
I'm afraid it'll
have to be brief.

982
00:37:59,580 --> 00:38:01,081
I wouldn't want to
be in those shoes.

983
00:38:01,114 --> 00:38:02,816
Whose shoes,
Mark's or the wife's?

984
00:38:02,849 --> 00:38:03,984
Neither.

985
00:38:07,420 --> 00:38:10,824
Sometimes I hesitate with a
family before I give the news.

986
00:38:10,857 --> 00:38:12,325
I know I'm going
to say something

987
00:38:12,358 --> 00:38:13,760
that will change
their lives forever.

988
00:38:13,794 --> 00:38:15,328
You just think that
if you don't say it

989
00:38:15,361 --> 00:38:16,963
it'll be okay for
a little while longer.

990
00:38:16,997 --> 00:38:20,066
I told this one mother
that her son had been killed

991
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:23,469
and she said, "Is it broken?"

992
00:38:23,504 --> 00:38:25,939
I'm looking at her and I didn't
know what she was saying.

993
00:38:25,972 --> 00:38:29,743
So she said,
"His arm, is it broken?

994
00:38:29,776 --> 00:38:31,344
'cause he's
pitching tomorrow."

995
00:38:31,377 --> 00:38:33,046
Then she just walked away.

996
00:38:33,079 --> 00:38:35,081
'Did you just let
her leave like that?'

997
00:38:35,115 --> 00:38:37,884
No, no, I called Carol,
I had her take care of it.

998
00:38:37,918 --> 00:38:40,921
That's a true story.

999
00:38:40,954 --> 00:38:44,525
At least...at least we..

1000
00:38:44,558 --> 00:38:45,992
...shot those videos of us

1001
00:38:46,026 --> 00:38:49,029
on the playground,
me and him, huh?

1002
00:38:49,062 --> 00:38:50,864
‐ Theo..
‐ It's a good thing.

1003
00:38:50,897 --> 00:38:53,767
I mean, TJ will be
able to see

1004
00:38:53,800 --> 00:38:56,770
what his daddy...look like,
used to be like.

1005
00:38:56,803 --> 00:38:59,573
You're gonna be that way again.
You hear me, Theo?

1006
00:38:59,606 --> 00:39:02,475
We are not giving
up that easy.

1007
00:39:02,509 --> 00:39:06,479
His blood gas showed PO‐2,
65 and PCO‐2 50.

1008
00:39:06,513 --> 00:39:08,515
We're standing by
with Versed.

1009
00:39:08,549 --> 00:39:10,016
Dr. Greene, look,
Dr. Carter needs you now!

1010
00:39:10,050 --> 00:39:11,618
I'll be there in a minute.

1011
00:39:11,652 --> 00:39:13,687
I'm afraid we have
to interrupt.

1012
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,021
Just another minute,
please?

1013
00:39:15,055 --> 00:39:17,090
Can you get somebody to
drive her home, please?

1014
00:39:17,123 --> 00:39:20,126
Theo, stop bossing me around.
I'm staying right here.

1015
00:39:20,160 --> 00:39:21,828
Pulse ox is down to 89.

1016
00:39:21,862 --> 00:39:22,929
He's getting dusky.

1017
00:39:22,963 --> 00:39:25,666
Two of Versed.

1018
00:39:25,699 --> 00:39:27,668
We can't wait any longer.

1019
00:39:27,701 --> 00:39:31,404
Once this sedative takes effect,
I'll intubate your husband.

1020
00:39:31,437 --> 00:39:32,939
Theo, when you wake up

1021
00:39:32,973 --> 00:39:34,841
you're gonna have a tube
helping you to breathe.

1022
00:39:34,875 --> 00:39:36,643
Mark, you mind
if we interrupt?

1023
00:39:36,677 --> 00:39:38,879
Ms. Cruz wanted to let you know
her brother came out of surgery.

1024
00:39:38,912 --> 00:39:40,647
The head CT showed no
bleeding in the brain.

1025
00:39:40,681 --> 00:39:43,917
That is really good news.
Thank you.

1026
00:39:43,950 --> 00:39:45,519
The boy's gonna be okay?

1027
00:39:45,552 --> 00:39:47,754
Yes, sir.
Thank you.

1028
00:39:47,788 --> 00:39:49,022
You saved my
brother's life.

1029
00:39:49,055 --> 00:39:50,791
That's good.

1030
00:39:52,826 --> 00:39:54,127
Can you feel that, honey?

1031
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,962
‐ Oh, yeah.
‐ Okay.

1032
00:40:08,542 --> 00:40:09,743
'I'm in.'

1033
00:40:11,645 --> 00:40:13,580
Is he breathing?

1034
00:40:13,614 --> 00:40:15,616
'We're breathing
for him now.'

1035
00:40:15,649 --> 00:40:17,818
'Dr. Greene, look,
you need to come now!'

1036
00:40:17,851 --> 00:40:20,020
'Excuse me.'

1037
00:40:28,895 --> 00:40:31,665
‐ What happened?
‐ He went into fib. Clear!

1038
00:40:31,698 --> 00:40:33,567
I've shocked him five times.
He went into asystole.

1039
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:34,768
I've given high dose
EPI and atropine.

1040
00:40:34,801 --> 00:40:36,036
Charge it again,
Malik to 360!

1041
00:40:36,069 --> 00:40:37,470
‐ 'Why didn't you call me?'
‐ I did.

1042
00:40:37,504 --> 00:40:38,805
‐ 'Yeah, two minutes ago.'
‐ Clear!

1043
00:40:40,073 --> 00:40:41,508
Charge it again, Malik.

1044
00:40:41,542 --> 00:40:42,643
I was following
the ACLS algorithms.

1045
00:40:42,676 --> 00:40:44,144
I thought I could handle it.

1046
00:40:44,177 --> 00:40:45,712
‐ Charge it again, Malik!
‐ Go ahead and call it.

1047
00:40:45,746 --> 00:40:47,047
Clear!

1048
00:40:47,080 --> 00:40:48,882
‐ Call it, Dr. Carter!
‐ Charge it again.

1049
00:40:48,915 --> 00:40:50,617
No rhythm.

1050
00:40:54,521 --> 00:40:55,889
Time of death is 9:56.

1051
00:40:55,922 --> 00:40:57,624
Call an attending when
there's a full arrest.

1052
00:40:57,658 --> 00:40:59,626
You get help.
You don't try and play the hero.

1053
00:40:59,660 --> 00:41:01,828
‐ I've run them before.
‐ That was up in surgery.

1054
00:41:01,862 --> 00:41:03,530
You work here now.

1055
00:41:12,038 --> 00:41:13,940
Did I miss anything?

1056
00:41:14,875 --> 00:41:16,743
Not that I can see.

1057
00:41:19,913 --> 00:41:22,649
I'm sorry, I didn't think
I was gonna lose him.

1058
00:41:25,151 --> 00:41:26,853
I'll sign the code sheet.

1059
00:41:26,887 --> 00:41:28,088
I'll do it.

1060
00:41:43,570 --> 00:41:44,605
'Do you want that interview?'

1061
00:41:44,638 --> 00:41:46,172
‐ 'Yes.'
‐ 'Do you?'

1062
00:41:46,206 --> 00:41:47,708
'You willing to answer
our questions?'

1063
00:41:47,741 --> 00:41:49,776
As long as you don't use
what you just shot.

1064
00:41:49,810 --> 00:41:50,944
'The walk‐away?'

1065
00:41:50,977 --> 00:41:53,079
The whole thing,
him losing the patient

1066
00:41:53,113 --> 00:41:54,147
me chewing him out.

1067
00:41:54,180 --> 00:41:55,582
It wasn't bad,
you know‐‐

1068
00:41:55,616 --> 00:41:57,050
‐ Do you want the interview?
‐ Yes.

1069
00:41:57,083 --> 00:41:58,852
Okay.

1070
00:41:58,885 --> 00:42:01,588
Look, I need a death
kit in here.

1071
00:42:15,969 --> 00:42:18,138
Probably the best
part of my job

1072
00:42:18,171 --> 00:42:20,841
is that sometimes,
working here

1073
00:42:20,874 --> 00:42:23,677
you can repair
some of the violence.

1074
00:42:23,710 --> 00:42:26,913
Some of the bad things
that happen to people.

1075
00:42:26,947 --> 00:42:28,715
Not always.

1076
00:42:28,749 --> 00:42:31,952
We couldn't do much for
that guy who was paralyzed

1077
00:42:31,985 --> 00:42:35,321
probably on a vent
for the rest of his life.

1078
00:42:35,355 --> 00:42:39,726
I guess we did save the kid
that he was trying to help.

1079
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:43,864
So, his sacrifice
wasn't for nothing.

1080
00:42:43,897 --> 00:42:47,133
And, yes...
I was attacked myself

1081
00:42:47,167 --> 00:42:50,170
right here in this hospital.

1082
00:42:50,203 --> 00:42:52,372
They haven't been able
to catch the guy who did it

1083
00:42:52,405 --> 00:42:56,610
or at least they haven't been
able to charge anyone.

1084
00:42:58,745 --> 00:43:04,184
The worst thing about it
isn't what it did to me.

1085
00:43:04,217 --> 00:43:06,720
The worst thing is
that it meant that some

1086
00:43:06,753 --> 00:43:10,824
of the world's violence
has leaked into our own ER.

1087
00:43:10,857 --> 00:43:14,227
This is meant to be a safe
place for fixing people.

1088
00:43:15,762 --> 00:43:17,998
Now it's vulnerable.

1089
00:43:18,031 --> 00:43:22,936
And as an ER doctor,
that's hard to accept.

1090
00:43:22,969 --> 00:43:25,806
'Sounds frightening.'

1091
00:43:25,839 --> 00:43:27,908
'Are you scared?'

1092
00:43:27,941 --> 00:43:29,676
Sure.

1093
00:43:29,710 --> 00:43:33,046
Of, uh, losing control.

1094
00:43:33,079 --> 00:43:35,081
'Control of what's outside?'

1095
00:43:37,117 --> 00:43:38,985
And what's in me.

1096
00:43:42,989 --> 00:43:44,024
Is that enough?

1097
00:43:44,057 --> 00:43:45,892
'Yes.'

1098
00:43:45,926 --> 00:43:47,794
Then turn it off.
